                <p class="text">
                    An operable vehicle is in good operating order and can move forward and backward without the assistance of humans. Inoperable or non-running vehicles are those that are unable to move. In this case, the driver will require a winch, which may incur additional costs. To put it another way, the customer must pay the driver more money for this additional service to be provided. Not every transportation company, however, provides this service with non-operational vehicles.


